    "description_long": "This is a small, enclosed grave plot featuring a prominent Celtic cross monument made of stone, mounted on a stepped pedestal. The grave area is surrounded by a decorative wrought iron fence, enclosing two flat stone grave markers with engraved symbols and possible inscriptions. The ground within the enclosure is covered with grass and patches of earth, while the base of the cross and the grave markers show signs of weathering. The cross itself is intricately carved with traditional Celtic knotwork and stands as the central focal point. The overall scene suggests a historical or memorial site, likely found in a park, churchyard, or urban cemetery.",
